Happy heavenly birthday Blake. ❤️ 3/14 is YOUR day. I’ve taken the day off to honor and remember you.  Not that I’ve forgotten but on this day I will allow myself even more time to sit in remembrance of you despite the pain that remembering causes because I don’t want to forget.

I remember becoming a mom for the first time 4 years ago, the labor pains, the trip to the hospital, the moment I met you, the weather on the day we brought you home,  how I was so stressed about the car seat and whether you were in it properly.  You were.  How slow and carefully we drove to ensure that we’d make it home safely with our new precious cargo. We did.

In a perfect world, today I’d  be prepping for your 4th birthday.  Im still struggling to figure out the “perfect” tradition to mark this day to honor you in a way that aligns with how deeply I love and miss you. I’ll keep thinking about it and trying new things each year. 

I love you beyond what language can accurately describe.  Everyday you’re my first thought when I wake and my last thought when I close my eyes at night.  I  think of you many times a day but especially on this day I wonder what you would be like now?  My guess is you’d be equal parts fun, funny and bossy. 

Raising awareness and funds for the thing I lost you to, pediatric cancer, is how I continue to mother you even though you’re not physically here. In honor of my sweet Blake please consider saying yes every time the cashier at the checkout counter asks if you’d like to “round up” your total to make a donation 
for childhood cancer research. When you’re thinking of a charitable cause to donate to please consider childhood cancer. You can also make a donation to the BlakeStarFund.org in Blake’s honor because Blake should be here. Happy 4th birthday my sweet boy 🎂 I’m so proud to be your mom. Love you forever, mommy ❤️🕊👼#teamBlakey
